Nigerian afropop sensation, Joeboy has bagged an ambassadorial deal with mobile gadget company, Samsung. <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/C79AB06D-40BE-4A62-A2BC-EFF83ECD9939-427x420.jpeg"/> In an official press statement, Iretiogo Oke, Head of marketing at Samsung Nigeria described Joeboy’s signing as a means to connect with customers through music. He said; “We want to further connect with our customers at all touch points, especially through music, which is one of the passions of people worldwide” He also talked about the company’s commitment to its customers in the new year. “With the launch of the galaxy A12, Samsung Nigeria has entered a new year with a strong commitment to providing Galaxy fans with the amazing features at an unbelievable price.” An excited Joeboy took to his Twitter account on the 8th of January 2021 to announce the deal. He said; “Excited to announce that I am now part of the @samsungmobileng family! #Celebration time Young Legend x Samsung Mobile #GalaxyAseries” <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2559BC33-0F17-43C3-9D3F-8F265D048FFA-640x395.jpeg"/> Congratulations Joeboy!! The post Joeboy Bags Samsung Ambassadorial Deal appeared first on Most Trusted Voice in Music & Afrobeats from Nigeria & Africa | Notjustok. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.